About Sarasota Film Festival
The Sarasota Film Festival, founded in 1998, is an international film festival hosted in Sarasota, Florida and viewable from around the world. The festival is typically held each April, in support of its mission: t
o celebrate the art of filmmaking and the contribution of filmmakers by hosting an international film festival and developing year-long programs for the economic, educational, and cultural benefit of our community
.
Frequently Asked Questions
When is the 2022 Sarasota Film Festival?
The
24th
Annual Sarasota Film Festival will run from April 1st – 10th, 2022.
How do I find out about the films, events, and parties?
Information about every Festival film and event is in the Film Guide! Each year, our digital Film Guide is available online, and hard copies are available at various businesses around town, and at our Box Office.
View our schedule for more information.
How much do film tickets cost?
Final 2022 prices yet to be announced, but in previous festivals the prices have been:
$15 – General public
$11 – SFF Members
Click here to learn more about becoming a member.
$10 – Students, Educators, and School Administrators (with valid ID)
Children 12 and under may attend all SFF youthFEST films for FREE. Tickets are required and may be obtained at the SFF Box Office.
DAY OF TICKETS
Films that are close to selling out go into “DAY OF” mode, with some tickets placed on reserve for pass-holders and filmmakers. If more general public tickets can be released, they are sold at the “Day Of” price on the day of the show. To avoid paying the higher price, we encourage patrons to consider buying SFF memberships, which allow for ticket sales before the general public, exclusive discounts and a host of other benefits that can be found
here
.
Here are the “DAY OF” ticket prices:
REGULAR: $22/public and $16/members
MATINEE: $15/public and $11/members
SPOTLIGHT/CENTERPIECE: $30/public and $22/members
Please come to the SFF Box Office with any questions, comments or concerns, or email the box office team at
boxoffice@sarasotafilmfestival.com
.
What are the Box Office hours?
@Sarasota Municipal Auditorium
801 N. Tamiami Trail, Sarasota, FL 34236
Box Office Open Daily APRIL 1-10, 2022 8:30 AM – 9:15 PM
@CMX CinéBistro Siesta Key
3501 S. Tamiami Trail, Suite 1100, Sarasota, FL 34239
Box Office Open Daily APRIL 2-10, 2022 5:30 PM – 7:00 PM
Call the Box Office 941-366-6200 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM
What if there’s a film I want to see and tickets are not available?
New Policy to be announced for SFF 2022
Where should I stay when visiting the Sarasota Film Festival?
Visit our
Plan Your Visit
section for special offers from our partner airport and hotels.
Does SFF offer any education programs? For adults, too?
The SFF Education department offers a variety of in-classroom and out-of-classroom education programs, for students from elementary school through adulthood, at no cost. To learn more about our year-round education and outreach initiatives, visit the “Community” section of our website.
Can I volunteer at the Sarasota Film Festival? Can I earn service hours?
Absolutely! Our volunteer work force is key to the success of our festival, and since we are a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization, you can earn service hours for your school. Find out more information about volunteering by
CLICKING HERE.
I want to help SFF, but I don’t have time to volunteer. What can I do?
You can help SFF continue and expand its programming year-round by
becoming an SFF Member
, or make a tax-deductable donation to The Sarasota Film Festival, Inc. Please email
development@sarasotafilmfestival.com
for more information about donating to our mission.

Support Sarasota Film Festival
The Sarasota Film Festival is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization that has been widely received as an artistic and cultural institution in Sarasota for 20 years strong. We rely on the support of generous donors, members, volunteers and business sponsors to bring our mission to fruition: to celebrate the art of filmmaking and the contribution of filmmakers by hosting an international film festival, and by developing year-round programs for the economic, educational, and cultural benefit of the greater Sarasota community.
